1. **Precision**: Each bounding box should perfectly enclose one single target object. In this image, both bounding boxes correctly enclose one crawler excavator each. The bounding boxes do not include any other objects.

2. **Recall**: All target objects should be localized by a bounding box. In this image, there are two crawler excavators, and both are enclosed by bounding boxes.

3. **Fit**: Each bounding box should neither be too loose nor too tight. The bounding boxes in this image are well-fitted around the crawler excavators. They do not cut off significant parts of the excavators and do not include excessive background.
